<paragraph id="8B9898347E5AFFD6FF3F72D6DEB0FC8F" blockId="40.[192,1441,508,884]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5AFFD6FF3F72D6DE4CFDEF" bold="true" box="[192,338,508,532]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Definition.</emphasis>
A genus in the same clade with 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E5AFFD6FD0972D6DB33FDEF" authority="Fabricius, 1793" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1793" box="[758,1069,508,532]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5AFFD6FD0972D6DC7CFDE8" box="[758,866,508,531]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Hesperia</emphasis>
Fabricius, 1793
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="549C26967E5AFFD6FBC072D6DB6BFDEF" box="[1087,1141,508,532]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E5AFFD6FB1972D6DE9EFDCF" authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comma">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5AFFD6FB1972D6DA81FDE8" box="[1254,1439,508,532]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Papilio comma</emphasis>
Linnaeus, 1758
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E5AFFD6FE6B7136DDD3FDCF" authority="Scudder, 1872" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1872" box="[404,717,540,564]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Atalopedes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5AFFD6FE6B7136DD06FDCF" box="[404,536,540,564]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Atalopedes</emphasis>
Scudder, 1872
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="549C26967E5AFFD6FD227136DC0DFDCF" box="[733,787,540,564]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E5AFFD6FC877136DBE8FDCF" authority="Edwards, 1863" authorityName="Edwards" authorityYear="1863" box="[888,1270,540,564]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huron">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5AFFD6FC877136DB2BFDCF" box="[888,1077,540,564]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Hesperia huron</emphasis>
Edwards, 1863
</taxonomicName>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E5AFFD6FABF7136DD87FDAF" authority="Skinner and Williams, 1923" authorityName="Skinner and Williams" authorityYear="1923" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pseudocopaeodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5AFFD6FABF7136DE26FDAF" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Pseudocopaeodes</emphasis>
Skinner and Williams, 1923
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="549C26967E5AFFD6FD557116DDFEFDAF" box="[682,736,572,596]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E5AFFD6FCB97116DBC9FDAF" authority="Edwards, 1881" authorityName="Edwards" authorityYear="1881" box="[838,1239,572,596]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Copaeodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eunus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5AFFD6FCB97116DB0BFDA8" box="[838,1045,572,596]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Copaeodes eunus</emphasis>
Edwards, 1881
</taxonomicName>
), but not closely related with any particular one. 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E5AFFD6FDC27177DC56FD8F" authority="Evans, 1955" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1955" box="[573,840,604,628]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pompeius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5AFFD6FDC27177DDAFFD8F" box="[573,689,605,628]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Pompeius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E5AFFD6FD497177DC56FD8F" author="Evans" box="[694,840,604,628]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans, 1955</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="549C26967E5AFFD6FCA97176DC95FD8F" box="[854,907,604,628]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E5AFFD6FC167177DA8CFD8F" authority="Latreille, [1824]" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1824" box="[1001,1426,604,628]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pompeius">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5AFFD6FC167177DBD5FD8F" box="[1001,1227,605,628]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Hesperia pompeius</emphasis>
Latreille, [1824]
</taxonomicName>
), where species from this genus were placed previously, is in a different clade from them (
<figureCitation id="131C84B17E5AFFD6FB077156DA51FD6F" box="[1272,1359,636,660]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="39.[192,275,1562,1584]" captionTargetBox="[192,1438,215,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[192,1440,213,1528]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Figure 13. Genomic trees of Hesperiina, Pericharini and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677261" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677261/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Keys to M.15.2 or M. 
<quantity id="4CDF35D17E5AFFD6FE8471B6DECEFD4F" box="[379,464,668,692]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.937" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" unit="in" value="15.5">15.5 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E5AFFD6FE2871B7DD62FD4F" author="Evans" box="[471,636,668,692]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans (1955)</bibRefCitation>
. Distinguished from its relatives by divided uncus with short and stout arms; thin gnathos arms, longer than uncus; valva with harpe about half of its length, unturned, terminating with two broad teeth directed dorsocaudad, no bristles; apiculus of six segments, nudum not black; stigma tripartite on dorsal forewing of males; pale spot distad of stigma segment in dorsal forewing cell CuA 
<subScript id="17A39A717E5AFFD6FE637006DEBBFCC1" attach="left" box="[412,421,812,826]" fontSize="6" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">1</subScript>
-CuA 
<subScript id="17A39A717E5AFFD6FE1B7006DEF3FCC1" attach="left" box="[484,493,812,826]" fontSize="6" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">2</subScript>
occupies the whole width of the cell. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly443.32.2:G99C, aly2487.36.2: 
<specimenCode id="DB81304F7E5AFFD6FCA17017DC84FCAE" box="[862,922,829,853]" collectionCode="T" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">T119</specimenCode>
G, aly443.32.2:A97G, aly887.14.12:A1715G, aly2096.38.5:A32C.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33DCBBF7E5AFFD6FF3F70A7DC21FBFE" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9898347E5AFFD6FF3F70A7DA9AFC5F" blockId="40.[192,1412,909,933]" box="[192,1412,909,933]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5AFFD6FF3F70A7DE45FC5E" bold="true" box="[192,347,909,933]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name, a feminine noun in the nominative singular, reflects the 
<typeStatus id="549C26967E5AFFD6FB6070A7DBCAFC5E" box="[1183,1236,909,933]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">type</typeStatus>
species name.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E5AFFD6FF3F7096DB14FC2E" blockId="40.[192,1034,956,981]" box="[192,1034,956,981]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5AFFD6FF3F7096DEAEFC2F" bold="true" box="[192,432,956,980]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Species included.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="549C26967E5AFFD6FE127097DD3CFC2E" box="[493,546,957,981]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">type</typeStatus>
species and 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E5AFFD6FD427097DB19FC2E" authority="Plotz, 1883" authorityName="Plotz" authorityYear="1883" box="[701,1031,956,981]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dares">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5AFFD6FD427097DC6AFC2F" box="[701,884,956,980]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Hesperia dares</emphasis>
Plötz, 1883
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E5AFFD6FF3F70C7DC21FBFE" blockId="40.[192,831,1005,1029]" box="[192,831,1005,1029]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">
